14:["$","p",null,{"className":"x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:leading-7","children":["WorldStateEngine learns about domains from ",["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"workspace/domains.yaml"}]," and per-project ",["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"domains.yaml"}]," files (discovered via ",["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"projects.yaml"}],"). This is loaded at startup via a ",["$","code",null,{"className":"nextra-code","dir":"ltr","children":"discoverAndRegister()"}]," call, not hardcoded."]}]
15:["$","p",null,{"className":"x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:leading-7","children":"The key decision here is that domain configuration lives outside the codebase. You can change which services are monitored by editing YAML files, without redeploying. This matters in production: adding a new service to monitor shouldn’t require a code review and deployment pipeline."}]
16:["$","p",null,{"className":"x:not-first:mt-[1.25em] x:leading-7","children":"Per-project domains allow each project to define the world-state data it cares about. A project with a custom CI system can add a domain for it without polluting the global domain config."}]
